sudokuGame

Class BoardIndividual

  • java.lang.Object
    • sudokuGame.Individual
      • sudokuGame.BoardIndividual
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>, Variable

    public class BoardIndividual
extends Individual
    BoardIndividual is representing the player that trying to solve the sudoku board, this class is extend Individual abstract class and implement the abstract method evaluate that call play method that will try to solve the sudoku board according to the tree-based GP, and return the fitness of the BoardIndividual. The fitness is the amount of the empty cells that remain until solve the whole sudoku board, remain zero cells mean that we succeed to solve the sudoku board and it's the ideal fitness.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Abedalrhman Nsasra
    See Also:
    Individual, Population, Genetic Programming

      • evaluateGradeboard

        void evaluateGradeboard()
        Evaluate the gradeboard (2D array) that hold in every cell a hash table (map), the hash table holds as a keys the possible numbers that can inserted without conflict in the current index, and as a values grades for the keys that represent how much good is the key as a solution. Smaller is better. So this method is evaluate and build this gradeboard.

      • initializeGradeboard

        void initializeGradeboard()
        Find which numbers can inserted in every cell without conflict, with the solved cells, and saves these number in gradeboard. The implementation is NOT efficient, we can optimize these code.

      • nextInc1ExcMax

        private int nextInc1ExcMax(int max)
        This method gives you a random number between 1 (inclusive) and max (exclusive), this method give a number in range [min,max) . This method act in strange way: if you call it with (1) argument it will return : 1 and if you run it with (2) argument it's rerun : 1 and if you run it with (0) argument it's return : 1 and if you run it with (3) argument it's return : 1 or 2 it's return a random number of focusing on min number is 1, if you send max number larger than 1, then it will return number in range exclusive max. We using it in mutate method, it's very important method.
        Parameters:
        max - is the max limit of the range that we want to generate number from it.
        Returns:
        a random number in the range 1 (inclusive) to max (exclusive).
